e460f4f93817bea10b2fba8aaddeb892421d2668.commit.message:
Avoid fine-sensitivity when testing freeSpace

Instead of a fixed delta of 256 kB, assume disk space does not change by
more than 1% between calling freeSpacfe and the second call to
freeSpaceKb - e.g. 1 GB on a 100 GB drive. 1% is still small enough to
detect if the code accidentally changes from kibibytes (1024) to
kilobytes (1000)
